13/04/2006
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Nine officials have been arrested as part of a sweeping operation against public sector corruption, according to press reports in Belgrade Thursday (13 April). Police reportedly questioned the chief of the Belgrade commercial court, Goran Kljajevic, as well as Judge Delinka Djurdjevic, Police Inspector Dejan Ivezic, head of the Postal Savings Bank Jelica Zivkovic, head of the Credit Export Bank Sekula Pjevcevic and four lawyers. A search for a seventh official, Slobodan Radulovic, former manager of the C Market company, is under way. All are suspected of misappropriation in several privatisation and bankruptcy procedures. (Blic, Danas, Politika - 13/04/06)
